"{\"uid\": \"irishtimes.com-opinion-2024-08-04-rite-and-reason-olympics-opening-event-was-about-defiance-not-inclusiveness\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"It was hardly surprising that the drag-queen parody of the Last Supper that opened the Paris Olympics on July 26th met widespread disapproval.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 142, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the drag-queen parody\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 51}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 70}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 101}, {\"ngram\": \"July 26th\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 114}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread disapproval\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seems to me that this came as no surprise to the parody's organisers either.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no surprise\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 187}, {\"ngram\": \"the parody's organisers\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 214}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, I would suggest that on their own terms they hit the bullseye.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 226, \"to\": 230}, {\"ngram\": \"their own terms\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 271}, {\"ngram\": \"the bullseye\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In recent days, a lot of commentary on the production has been asking why Christian faith and the sensibilities of its adherents were targeted in such a way.\", \"from\": 296, \"to\": 453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999904794152199, \"rank\": 9.520675231125903e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"recent days\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 310}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 317}, {\"ngram\": \"commentary\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 331}, {\"ngram\": \"the production\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 349}, {\"ngram\": \"the sensibilities\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"its adherents\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"such a way\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 452}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it, for instance, that elements of France's cultural elite are afraid of the lingering influence of Catholicism, and are desperate (how desperate can one be?)\", \"from\": 454, \"to\": 615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8001439631065522, \"rank\": 0.16432035720572877, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"elements\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"the lingering influence\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 610}]}, {\"sentence\": \"to weaken the faith by means of ridicule?\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 657, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"means\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"ridicule\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whatever the accuracy of such conjectures, I think that it is important to look not only at what the production targeted, but also at the mentality behind the production.\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the accuracy\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"such conjectures\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 700}, {\"ngram\": \"the production\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"the mentality\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"the production\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The deepest purpose and intent of the parody with that the Olympics opened was not to scandalise or to offend (both of that it most certainly did), but to transgress.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The deepest purpose\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"intent\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"the parody\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transgression has become a key concept for understanding our present cultural moment.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Transgression\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"a key concept\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"our present cultural moment\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In recent decades, an entire academic discipline, Queer Theory, has arisen in universities.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Queer Theory\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"recent decades\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1102}, {\"ngram\": \"an entire academic discipline\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1133}, {\"ngram\": \"universities\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its purpose is to question, problematise, subvert and finally transgress distinctions between right and wrong, good and bad, beautiful and ugly, normal and abnormal.\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its purpose\", \"from\": 1177, \"to\": 1188}, {\"ngram\": \"distinctions\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"right\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Queer Theory, the primary sites of such transgression are sexuality and gender, but the same \\\"queering\\\" is proposed for culture as a whole.\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Queer Theory\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queer_theory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the primary sites\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"such transgression\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"sexuality\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"the same \\\"queering\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As is widely known, the word \\\"queer\\\" has often been used as a deliberately offensive version of the word \\\"homosexual\\\" Given this history, it may be necessary to clarify that the significance of the term has changed, and it is now used dispassionately by both the advocates and the opponents of queer theory.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"queer\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"a deliberately offensive version\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1581}, {\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"this history\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"the significance\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"the term\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"both the advocates\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"the opponents\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"queer theory\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The adjective \\\"queer\\\" and the verb \\\"to queer\\\" are found throughout the abundant academic literature.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The adjective \\\"queer\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1817}, {\"ngram\": \"the verb\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1831}, {\"ngram\": \"the abundant academic literature\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, what has all of this got to do with the Parisian parody?\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Parisian parody\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather a lot.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rather a lot\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Queering is partly about transgression, and the Olympic Games drag-queen Last Supper was a mammoth exercise in transgression.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2099, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Queering\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"transgression\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games drag-queen Last Supper\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"a mammoth exercise\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"transgression\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its producers, strange to say, showed an instinct for the sacred that would put many devout Catholics to shame.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.44195158079681e-13, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its producers\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"an instinct\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2150}, {\"ngram\": \"shame\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They identified the sacred, they pursued it, and they targeted it precisely to transgress it.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2306, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By way of apology, spokespersons and directors defaulted to notions of inclusiveness, goodwill, generosity and solidarity, thereby inviting - in a transgressively subtle way - all objectors who share these values to put up, shut up, and grow up.\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"way\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"apology\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"spokespersons\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2340}, {\"ngram\": \"directors\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"notions\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2375}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusiveness\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"goodwill\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"generosity\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"solidarity\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"a transgressively subtle way\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2481}, {\"ngram\": \"all objectors\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"these values\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2520}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In itself, the issue of apology is neither here nor there, but that non-apology typifies an approach to argumentation commonly used by queer theory and its activists.\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the issue\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"apology\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2586}, {\"ngram\": \"that non-apology typifies\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"an approach\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2655}, {\"ngram\": \"argumentation\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2672}, {\"ngram\": \"queer theory\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"its activists\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An outlandish statement is made, and when the predictable backlash occurs, the activists retreat, temporarily, to ideas with that reasonable people can scarcely disagree.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An outlandish statement\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2745}, {\"ngram\": \"the predictable backlash\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2788}, {\"ngram\": \"the activists\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2810}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 2836, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"that reasonable people\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In this approach, the most used fallback notion is that of \\\"inclusiveness\\\", and in the present instance, the de facto social, moral and cultural exclusion of countless viewers by a parody of what they hold sacred was justified by an appeal to inclusiveness.\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this approach\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"the most used fallback notion\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"the present instance\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2997}, {\"ngram\": \"the de facto social, moral and cultural exclusion\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3048}, {\"ngram\": \"countless viewers\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"a parody\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3081}, {\"ngram\": \"an appeal\", \"from\": 3124, \"to\": 3133}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusiveness\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3150}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that sounds inconsistent, do not worry; it's simply a transgression of oppressive notions of consistency.\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3260, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a transgression\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3222}, {\"ngram\": \"oppressive notions\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3244}, {\"ngram\": \"consistency\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a striking passage of his New Testament letter to the Philippians, St Paul urges believers to think about \\\"whatever is true, noble, good, pure, honourable and praiseworthy\\\".\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3291, \"end\": 3304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Testament\", \"score\": 0.9999205446018826, \"rank\": 7.946166336294486e-05, \"text\": \"New Testament\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Testament\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Testament\"}, {\"begin\": 3319, \"end\": 3330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Philippians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Philippians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Philippians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a striking passage\", \"from\": 3265, \"to\": 3283}, {\"ngram\": \"St Paul\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3339}, {\"ngram\": \"believers\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3355}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not only Christian believers who consider these.\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3454, \"end\": 3463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999904794152199, \"rank\": 9.520675231125903e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are others who think about such things to transgress any ideas, any canons, by that anything might be reckoned honourable or praiseworthy.\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3638, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3504, \"to\": 3510}, {\"ngram\": \"such things\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3538}, {\"ngram\": \"any ideas\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3562}, {\"ngram\": \"any canons\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3574}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3584, \"to\": 3592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To quote a recent article on \\\"drag pedagogy\\\" in the classroom: \\\"There is a premium on standing out, on artfully desecrating the sacred.\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3774, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a recent article\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3664}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"drag pedagogy\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3682}, {\"ngram\": \"the classroom\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3700}, {\"ngram\": \"a premium\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3721}, {\"ngram\": \"the sacred\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3773}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, what we refer to as strategic defiance is encouraged.\\\"\", \"from\": 3775, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"strategic defiance\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3829}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris was not at all about inclusiveness; it was all about defiance and transgression.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3847, \"end\": 3852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9998681249168518, \"rank\": 0.00013189247632039574, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"defiance\", \"from\": 3906, \"to\": 3914}, {\"ngram\": \"transgression\", \"from\": 3919, \"to\": 3932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the mentality that gives rise to such things, there is no target, no moment at that we will have arrived at a fairer or more beautiful world.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4078, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mentality\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3950}, {\"ngram\": \"rise\", \"from\": 3962, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"such things\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3981}, {\"ngram\": \"no target\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 4001}, {\"ngram\": \"a fairer or more beautiful world\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4077}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There will only be further transgression of ideas of fairness and beauty.\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"further transgression\", \"from\": 4098, \"to\": 4119}, {\"ngram\": \"ideas\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4140}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 4145, \"to\": 4151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We can expect more of the same, until we make it clear that society and culture cannot be \\\"queered\\\" indefinitely.\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4267, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 4214, \"to\": 4221}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rev Dr Chris Hayden is a priest of the Diocese of Ferns \\u00a9 2025 The Irish Times DAC\", \"from\": 4269, \"to\": 4352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4282, \"end\": 4288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Hayden\", \"score\": 0.8958199775122123, \"rank\": 0.11607846683450299, \"text\": \"Hayden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Hayden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Hayden\"}, {\"begin\": 4333, \"end\": 4348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Irish_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Irish Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Irish_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Irish_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a priest\", \"from\": 4292, \"to\": 4300}, {\"ngram\": \"the Diocese\", \"from\": 4304, \"to\": 4315}, {\"ngram\": \"Ferns\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4324}]}]}"